# secret.yaml is a local-only credentials file derived from secret.yaml.template.
# It is never committed and never managed by GitOps.
# The deployed stack uses Vault: bootstrap/vault/vault-bootstrap.sh writes credentials
# to Vault KV v2, and the VaultStaticSecret CR (system/vault-config/vault-static-secret.yaml)
# syncs them to the kubernetes-agent K8s Secret automatically.
# secret.yaml.template IS tracked and defines the expected secret keys — keep it in sync.
**/secret.yaml
**/*.env
**/secrets.env
**/.env